inn1.comm: he starts off with an inswinging yorker, which is dug out with relative ease by the batsman
now a fuller length delivery from wide of the crease, the batsman lets it go through
he gets this one to nip back from back of length and surprises the batsman with the movement, Shehzad gets hit on the thigh pad
length delivery in the channel outside off, left alone with ease
he bowls it on back of length outside off, the batsman defends it off the back foot
first runs for Pakistan, Shehzad pushes the length delivery without any feet movement to the gap at cover for a single. He wanted a second, but was sent back in time
good teasing length from Holder, it's full and outside off, just straightens a touch too. The batsman leaves it alone
pulls the length back just a little bit, but keeps it there outside off. Shehzad leaves it alone
fuller again, this time the batsman takes a forward stride and defends it to cover
gets good bounce from a length and this one came in to the batsman too, Shehzad brings his bat down a little late in his defence
he bowls a wide down the leg side in an attempt to bowl a yorker
back to that tight line and length just outside off, Shehzad stays patient, leave it alone
angled in from wide of the crease, the batsman pushes it back to the bowler
he stays in the crease and defends his first delivery back to the bowler
angled across the left-hander, Jamshed covers the line of the stumps and lets it go through
oh beautifully timed this one! He takes a tiny step forward to this length delivery and drives it on the up past the left of a diving mid-off fielder
this time he stays in the crease and defends the back of length delivery to leg side
this one is quick, but a bit wide outside off, the batsman calmly lets it go
length delivery on off stump, Jamshed stays in the crease and defends it to midwicket
positive stride forward by the batsman and his push through extra cover beats the two fielders to the boundary. Samuels was after it, but slowed down and didn't make any effort
he does the Flamingo shot now! Stylishly tickles a back of length delivery on off to deep backward square leg
more positive strokemaking! He times this fuller delivery to the off side, but it is hit straight to cover
the bowler pushes this one a touch wider outside off, Shehzad lets it go through
fuller delivery outside off, Shehzad again moves forward and pushes it to the off side, finds the fielder, but shows he is looking very positive here
length delivery on off, he defends it to the off side this time
yes, no, yes, no! Jamshed calls for a single to midwicket, but is quickly sent back by Shehzad as Dwayne Bravo lunges towards the ball
he tries to push the length ball to off without moving forward, inside edges it on to his pads
this time he comes forward and steers the length delivery to third man for a couple
he gets behind this one and defends the back of length delivery back to the bowler
oh nicely punched off the front foot, but he finds the fielder at cover with that drive
edged and it just falls short of Sammy at second slip! Again, Jamshed chooses to stay on the back foot to a fullish delivery, gets a single down to third man
he bowls a short of length delivery to Jamshed, his first to the left-hander, the batsman defends it off the back foot
this one is too straight and the batsman clips it easily to fine leg for a single
bowls length outside off, there is good carry on this pitch as the keeper takes it chest high after the batsman has let it go through
back of length this time, the batsman defends it off the back foot
back of length again, but this time there is width on this one, Shehzad stands up on his toes and steers it past point and manages to beat the third-man fielder. Good timing on that one
fuller length delivery on off stump, the batsman defends it to off
he comes forward and steers the length delivery to third man
he bowls a fuller length delivery from wide of the crease, the batsman gets hit on the pads as he tries to push it to the leg side, but this was heading down leg
angled in from wide of the crease again, the batsman defends it to mid-on
back of length delivery on off stump, the batsman defends it to midwicket this time
fuller delivery this time and Shehzad comes forward and plays straight, defends it back to the bowler
there is a direct hit at the striker's end, but Jamshed makes it easily after Shehzad pushes a length delivery to mid-off and calls for a quick single
he sprays this down the leg side, Charles has to dive full length to get to that
slightly short and Shehzad immediately rocks back and swivels to pull it over square leg.. The ball however almost stops after hitting the ground and slows down at the boundary

dropped by Gayle! Oh this is a straightforward chance at first slip, waist high, right in the middle, goes in and pops out. The batsman had gone for a drive on a length ball.. What a reprieve! Holder was celebrating it already and had to turn back in disappointment
length delivery slightly wide outside off, the batsman leaves it alone this time
oh another outside edge after the batsman charges down the pitch to the bowler! this one flies fine on the off side and just bounces a few meters in front of the third-man fielder
he beats Jamshed with a length delivery outside off, the batsman didn't really come forward to cover the line of that one
length delivery on off stump, the batsman defends it to midwicket
he comes forward and defends the length delivery towards mid-off
the angle on that one saves the batsman! the bowler appeals for lbw, but that one cut in too far
length delivery on off stump, the batsman gets squared up a touch as he defends this
full delivery on the stumps, the batsman pushes it to midiwicket
he stays in the crease and defends the length delivery towards point
pulls the length back now, Shehzad defends it off the back foot solidly
he whips this length delivery to his preferred leg side again, straight to midwicket
he takes a forward stride and drives the length delivery over cover point, times it well but it again slows down in the heavy outfield
he stays in the crease and opens the face of the bat to run this down to third man
full and on the middle stump line, Shehzad drives it to mid-on
length delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and defends it to off
fuller length delivery wide outside off, the batsman attempts a cover drive, but it hits the inside half of the bat and goes towards mid-on
starts off with a length delivery on off, the batsman defends it off the back foot
he has had enough! He charges down the pitch and heaves the length delivery over mid-on, it just drops short of the boundary.. a few millimeters short of the boundary I say
he clips the length delivery to wide mid-on for a single
fuller delivery outside off, the batsman leans on this one and pushes it to deep point
he defends this back of length delivery off the back foot
he tries to crash this length delivery on the up, but is beaten by it. Sammy stands there nodding his head for a couple of seconds
full delivery on off stump, the batsman digs it out off the front foot
back of length delivery this time, defended to off
drives this one in the air again, over the infield and again, it slow down in the outfield..
he shuffles across to this full delivery and pushes it to cover where a slight misfield allows for a single

Has this been taken? Roach does that trick at the fine-leg boundary - he takes the catch, realises his falling over, pops it back in, goes out and comes back to complete the catch. But there is a problem, his left foot was too close the rope and the umpires are looking at it. But they are happy with it, Shehzad has to go. He top-edged his pull shot high and for a moment it looked like it was going to sail over the fielder. Good catch by Roach
gets a length delivery on the pads, which he is unable to get away with it. It hits the pads and rolls to the left of the keeper

another top-edge! another wicket! Sammy gets a wicket and the smallish crowd can be heard now. Jamshed makes mess of a decent start, he tried to pull this short of length delivery from outside off. It got a touch big on him and the top-edge settled into the hands of Roach at mid-on
he gets good bounce from just back of length, Misbah goes on the back foot and defends
length delivery outside off, Misbah lets it go through
fuller this time, the batsman comes forward and clips this one past midwicket for a couple of runs
back of length on off, the batsman nudges it to square leg for a quick single
he goes on the back foot and pushes the length delivery to cover
fuller delivery outside off, the batsman pushes it to mid-off
he comes forward and defends the length delivery to off side
length delivery wide outside off, the batsman lets it go
length delivery angled in, the batsman dabs it towards square leg for a quick single
short ball, pull shot, recipe for disaster.. well almost! This one just evades Dwayne Bravo at midwicket
length delivery outside off, left alone
length delivery on off stump, he comes forward and pushes it to mid-on
back of length on off this time, Prof drops it next to his boots
stays on the back foot to this length delivery and pushes it out to cover
goes for a yorker, easily dug out by the batsman
he goes on the back foot and pushes the back of length delivery to mid-on for a single
he stays on the back foot and defends this to gully
he comes forward and drives the length delivery to cover
this one is a good call for single! the batsman drops it to the off side and Misbah calls immediately
full and with a bit of width outside off, Misbah opens the face and just times it through cover point.. He didn't try to hit that hard at all, just pushes it in the gap
length delivery closer to the stumps, the batsman defends it off the front foot
shortish delivery this time, Misbah hops on his toes and defends it to off
shortish delivery again, Misbah dabs it to leg side and calls for a quick single
fullish on the off stump and Misbah moves across slightly and pushes it towards mid-on
keeps it tight and straight and he pushes it to the on side
tries to jab this away to the off side, slight width and extra bounce, he is beaten
drifts to the on side and he works it off his pads to the on side
stays back and he pushes it back to the bowler
good length on middle and leg and he tucks it to the on side
starts off round the wicket, full and worked to the on side
gives it more air and he plonks forward and defends
this one spins back in a little and the batsman knocks it to the on side
on the pads and he turns it to fine leg
stays back and works it with the turn to the leg side
Misbah gets well forward and defends this one, wonder if Narine will continue round the wicket
drifts it towards the pads and he knocks it to fine leg
holds the length back and he works it towards square leg
keeps it tight and he stays right back and defends
full and moving in and he gets well forward and pushes it to mid-off
slightly short and he stays back and knocks it to point
Hafeez pushes it towards cover and Misbah tells him to stay back
stays back and pushes it to the off side
stays back and works it with the turn to long-on
this was sliding outside off and he waited on it and cut it behind point
commits forward and gently works it behind square leg, settles for a single only
quicker delivery, slight change of action and it skids through and beats the outside edge
he stays back and pulls and it appears like it just drops short of Simmons at short midwicket, a good stop though to limit that to a single
just uses Sammy's angle and isn't afraid to glide that wide of first slip
Misbah takes the risk of playing the late cut and it just drops short of slip, Misbah smiles, he knows that was risky
moves back in and he works it to midwicket
tries to pinch it square on the off side but slip comes across and cuts it off
tight stuff again by Sammy, Misbah quietly knocks it to the on side
swings it towards the pads and he works it to square leg
chops it towards first slip
goes back at the crease and knocks it to short leg
full on the pads and he works it to short fine leg
skids through and hits the pads, Misbah was too late on the shot, extra bounce too
fullish and quicker and he turns it behind square leg
tossed up on middle and off and he gets well forward and defends
stays back and softly pushes this one to cover
he goes back at the crease and knocks it down the track
drifts on the pads and he uses the angle and turns it to fine leg

almost carried to the rope! Hafeez tucked it away wide of square leg and two fielders converged, the one from fine leg misfielded and his partner just managed to pull it back before the rope, close call
stays back and works it back to the bowler
stays beside the line and pushes it to point
plonks forward and defends to the off side
was Misbah reading your comments? Out of the blue he gets on  his knee and slogs clean over deep midwicket
comes forward and pushes it wide of mid-off
goes back and punches it to the on side
full on the pads and he knocks it wide of short fine leg
stays back and pushes it straight to square leg
tight line on middle stump, extra bounce and he is happy to defend
this was full on the pads and he flicks it and Gayle slides and stops it at short square leg

chance for a run-out! This was worked wide of midwicket and it was Misbah who called for the second almost immediately, he got to the other end and changed his mind and by then Hafeez was already halfway into the second run, throw at the wrong and Hafeez was able to scramble back
opens the face and runs it to third man
swings towards the pads and he works it to midwicket

Appeal for a lbw and he's been given not out and Sammy wants that reviewed, lands it outside off and nips back in, Misbah shuffled across the crease and tried to flick it to the on side, he was struck below the knee roll, looked like hitting leg stump, no contact with bat or glove, Hawkeye shows that only hitting the top of leg stump, not convincing enough so Reiffel's original decision stays
drifts on the pads and he works it to the on side
this was short down the leg side and he shapes to pull and a stifled appeal from the bowler as the ball passes the glove
sort down the leg side and another attempted pull, wide down the leg side
good length on middle and leg and he works it to midwicket
stays beside the line and he knocks it down to point
moves across his stumps and he's happy to defend this to cover
slower ball outside off and he opens the face and runs it to third man
short of a length and he works it to midwicket
tempts him with width and Misbah is beaten on the cut, should have put that away
full on the stumps and pushed to the on side
holds the length back and he softly pushes it towards short midwicket
this was well placed, drifting on the pads, he turns the face of the bat and turns it to fine leg, the fielder couldn't cut that off, that's the 50 stand, slow but steady
this was wide outside off and pushed to the off side

soft dismissal! Bravo continues with the short stuff to Hafeez, he can't resist going for the pull, gets a top edge and Sammy takes the easiest of catches at square leg, Hafeez beaten for a bit of pace too
the debutant gets a short one first up, round the wicket and he gets down quickly to evade that
outside edge but well short of first slip, he played it with soft hands
this was fuller outside off and he opens the face of the bat and gets off the mark with a dab to third man
slower ball and Misbah shuffles and pushes it down the track
shuffles again and he works a full ball down to long-on
good length on the off stump and he pushes it softly back to the bowler
same result, Misbah is happy to knock it back to the bowler
nips towards the pads and he works it with the angle to square leg
comes down the track and he pushes it down to cover
little shorter and he punches it towards cover
this was short outside off and he slashed it in the air but there was no backward point so a safe shot
tossed up and he comes forward and works it to mid-on
cuts it just wide of short third man and Misbah has to hurry
opens the face and cuts it down toshort  third man
full on middle and he defends
quicker delivery, cramped for the cut and he can't beat point
stays back and knocks it to the on side
full on the stumps and he flicks it down to deep midwicket
Bravo hammers it short down the leg side and Misbah doesn't bother playing at it
slower ball outside off and dead-batted to the off side
good length on middle and off and he softly pushes it down the track
another slower one and he pushes it on the up to long-on
a short one from Bravo and Sohail quickly gets down and evades that one
waits for it to turn before knocking it to the on side
flicks it firmly with the turn to square leg
Misbah gets on his knee and sweeps it down to fine leg
Sohail gets forward and drives straight to extra cover
stays back and knocks it wide of square leg
outside off and he cuts it straight to point
drifts on the pads and he works it to midwicket
slower ball and full on the pads, turns the face of the bat and works it wide of square leg
round the wicket to the left-hander and he ducks quickly to evade that bouncer
close to an edge! This one bounced a lot more off a good length and it surprised Sohail who tried to punch that away to the off side
on a good length but no alarming bounce, he punches it away
ends the over with another bouncer, ducks under it
Misbah moves across his crease and settles on defending it
chips down the track and checks his shot and defends
worked towards midwicket and Sohail sets off and he is sent back quickly
drifts on the pads and he knocks it to short fine leg
drifts on the pads and he fails to work it away to fine leg, slip darts across to try and cut that off
he stands tall and guides the short of length delivery to third man
another back of length delivery on the middle stump line, Sohail whips it to deep midwicket
another lifter outside off, he pushes that to point
dabs the back of length delivery to midwicket and thinks of a single, but is rightly sent back
some width available on this shortish delivery outside off, Misbah cuts it firmly, but Sammy at point dives and gets a hand to slow it down
he waits on the back foot and defends the back of length delivery back to the bowler
tossed up and full on off, Sohail drives it to long-off
bowls an offspinner this time which is tucked to square leg by Misbah for a single
he goes back to cut this offspinning delivery, but is beaten by the bounce on that and he gets a thick outside edge past the slip fielder for a boundary
tossed up on off stump, the batsman pushes it to deep midwicket for a single
flatter and shorter on off, Misbah pushes it to midwicket
flighted this time and he eases it to long-on
and he gets it with a soft push towards mid-on off a length delivery. 91 balls he has taken!
he bowls a short delivery at the youngster, who defends it to point
another shortish delivery, but it's on the leg stump line and Sohail clips it fine on the leg side for a couple
short of length delivery on the middle stump line, the batsman tries to play it towards point, but ends up dropping it down to his boots
short delivery on the body, Sohail was awkward on the shot as he tries to sway away, but ends up steering it through slip for a boundary
he comes forward and drives the length delivery straight to cover
bowls a quicker offspinner on the leg stump line, the batsman gets hit on the thigh pad
this one is heading down the leg side and Charles fails to collect it cleanly
WHoaaa! When he hits it, he hits it big! Tossed up outside off, Misbah goes down on his knee and whacks it over wide long on for a huge six
now he comes forward and defends the next one to the leg side
quicker offspinner outside off, Misbah dabs it to cover and calls for a quick single
quickish delivery outside off, the batsman opens the face to place it to point
another quicker one and Sohail, who was trying to make room, ends up pushing it back to the bowler
length delivery on off stump, the batsman pushes it softly towards midwicket for a single
loud appeal for caught behind as Sohail is beaten! He was making room to pierce the off side but is beaten by the bounce
short of length delivery on off, he gets up on his toes and guides it to third man
length delivery with some room outside off, he carves it over the fielder at cover point, but it slows down towards the boundary
fuller delivery, it is eased to long-on for a single
length delivery on off stump, the batsman pushes it to deep point for a single
he tried the cut in the last two overs, now he succeeds and this one races past backward point. Darren Bravo makes a sliding stop at the boundary. It is fifty of the partnership
shorter and on the stumps, the batsman pushes it back to the bowler
shorter and quicker this time, again pushes back to the bowler
this times he clips a similar delivery to backward square leg for a single
this ones goes the other way and Sohail had no idea about this. He was shaping to play a late cut, but it comes back into him
good early call for two to deep midwicket and the pressure put onto the fielders buys them an overthrow too
that was a good shot! It was short and wide and crunched off the back foot, but Pollard dives at point and saves a certain boundary
he jumps out of the crease very early and goes inside out over extra cover off a length delivery, the ball, slows down again
short of length delivery on the body, he smartly swivels to guide this to long leg
short delivery to test the youngster, who has been a bit circumspect against that sort of length
this wicket has come from nowhere! Sohail gets a short and wide dolly and he crashes it off the back foot again, but it's in the air and it's straight to Pollard at point, he gobbles it up
short of length delivery on off, the batsman tucks it to midwicket off the back foot
bowls a quicker one on the pads, the batsman defends it back to the bowler
oh this one is a bad delivery! He is bowling from round the wicket and he pushes this one down the leg side, the keeper didn't have much of a chance
pushed through on off stump, the batsman goes on the back foot and punches it to deep cover
he goes down on his knee to paddle this one, but makes no connection and gets hit on the pads
fuller delivery, he makes room and drives it firmly, but straight to mid-off
that is beautiful delivery! It was tossed up and drew the batsman forward and kept going away with the angle to beat the bat
pushed through on the middle and leg line, the batsman pushes it to midwicket
he fires this on the pads, Misbah gets his front leg out of the way and flicks it to fine leg
he moves outside leg stump to make room and slaps the back of length delivery without much timing to long-on
he jumps out of the crease, but gets a yorker, which he pushes towards long-on off the toe of his bat
almost plays it to the hands of Gayle at cover! he was trying to whip it to the leg side, but gets a leading edge
length delivery, Akmal attempts a heave to long-on, but gets an inside edge. Charles does well to dive to his left to stop a certain boundary
back of length delivery that follows Umar. The batsman works it to deep midwicket
he tosses it up, but it's Umar, not Misbah, batting. The batsman makes room and slams it over mid-off for a boundary
this one is fired on the pads and Umar sweeps it to fine leg
he walks way down the leg side too early, Narine fires one in and cramps him for room
pushed through on the pads, it is worked away to fine leg for a single
quicker delivery, but Umar is down the pitch anyway. He tries to whack it over midwicket, but gets a thich inside edge to deep backward square leg
fuller delivery on the pads, the batsman tries to paddle it fine, but is not able to beat the man at short fine
oh wow! It's Misbah's helicopter! It doesn't really take off the ground, but that was hit incredibly hard and beats the man at long-on easily
he bowls a low full toss on the pads, the batsman flicks it fine to deep backward square leg and steals a couple, dives to get in
he charges down too early and Bravo delivers a good yorker on the middle stump from round the wicket! Misbah is late to bring his bat down in time and sees his stumps splayed!
the 'real entertainer' gets a short delivery first up, he ducks under it
he gets another short ball and like most batsmen today, top-edges it. Luckily for him it drops safely at backward square leg

length delivery outside off, Umar pushes it to cover and thinks off a single, but Lil Bravo fires a throw in and hits the stumps direct. The ricochet allows an extra run, but the umpires check for a run-out. He is fine
he charges down the track to a short delivery, flat-bats it down to long-on
he makes room, but he gets a quick short ball that flies over his attempted swat
slower delivery from the big man! Afridi wanted to send it to the sea, but is beaten
well, almost everyone is top-edging and so does Boom Boom! Short ball, he goes for a pull, gets a thick top edge that flies to Narine at fine leg
he gets a short of length delivery that follows him as he tries to  make room, worked away to deep midwicket
back of length delivery on the pads, the batsman clips it off his hips to fine leg
short delivery on the body, Riaz tucks it to square leg for a single
beautifully hit! He makes room and creams the low full toss to deep extra cover boundary
charges down the pitch this time and takes the ball on the full, smashes it to the same region as the previous ball
and another one! But this one is very stylish. It was a yorker again, but he bends down and opens the face to place it fine on the off side, between the keeper and the short third man fielder
charges down too early, Bravo bowls a short one on off stump. The batsman dabs it to point for a single
he bowls another yorker, Wahab does well to guide it fine on the leg side. Umar says waapis aa waapis aa (come back for the second) and makes it easily

Riaz is safe at the non-striker's end as the bowler is unable to take the throw from the deep. The batsman gets a slower bouncer that he turns to deep square leg and calls for a non-existent second. What more, he ran a run short too
another slower bouncer, this time he plays it straight to midwicket
quicker short one this time! the batsman tries to swat it away, but misses as it flies past his bat, called a wide
slower short of length delivery, slapped straight to midwicket again
short delivery, Umar is out of the crease, he swats and misses again
now he gets one from the middle of the bat! This one didn't get up too much, and Umar, who was making room already, thwacked it through point
short slower ball, the batsman pulls it to backward square leg for a quick single
bowls a shortish slower ball, the batsman slaps it to mid-off for a single
he moves his front leg out and tries to tennis bat it over mid-off, but that digs into the turf as it lands
bowls a good yorker, the batsman gets a fine inside edge, but the keeper does well to stop that
oh Wahab you beauty! He goes down on his knee and carves a half-volley over extra cover with a lot of timing. It hits the rope on the full
short ball this time, Riaz swats it and does it well, this one sails over cow corner now
slower delivery wide outside off, the batsman drags it to long-on for a single
he bowls a wide from wide of the crease.. too much angle on that one
slower delivery on the body, the batsman tries to whack it to the leg side, but gets hit on the body
he cramps the batsman for room with a length delivery, the batsman tucks it to backward square leg
another one fired on the pads, the batsman doesn't get a bat on it as this one goes to short fine after hitting the pads
he jumps out of the crease early and gets a slower ball, he drags it to deep backward square leg and picks up a couple
he makes room and tries to go over long-off, but this one goes behind the stumps as the batsman gets a thick outside edge through slips for a boundary
slower delivery from wide of the crease, it's cut straight to short third man

inn2.comm: beautiful delivery to start off with! Landed on the corridor outside off and just moved away, close to the edge
Gayle is solid in defense this time, goes right behind the line and defends
drifts on the pads and a bit too straight, Gayle softly pushes it to midwicket
a bit too straight and Gayle eases it down to fine leg to get off the mark
142 kph, good bounce and carry to the keeper and well left by Charles
a misfield allows a boundary, Charles cleared the back leg and made room early to smash that, it was pitched up and Charles thrashed that straight to mid-off, Afridi wasn't sharp enough there

and Junaid makes an impact straightaway, he fires that full and gets it to swerve in, hits the front pad as Gayle looks to flick, the swing looked like it would take it past leg stump, confident appeal but Pakistan decide not to refer it
poses questions yet again with the inswing, it was an inside edge to the pads as replays showed, good that Pakistan didn't review that
confident shot past the covers, he found the gap but the outfield isn't quick enough
good length on middle and off and he stays back and defends
gets it to swing towards the off stump and Gayle pushes it to the off side
this was shorter in length but wide enough for Gayle to free his arms, punched on the up just wide of short extra cover, races to the boundary, good over nevertheless
short and wide and thumped to the off side and excellent stop by Shehzad at backward point, saved a few
Charles makes room and looks to slog it away, he ended up merely practicing his golf swing
drifts on the body and he tucks it away behind square on the on side
thick edge! Irfan bowled that on a good length outside off, straightened a bit and Charles was half forward and poked his bat at it, Akmal takes the edge
lands outside the off stump and he safely leaves it alone
he slides this one down the leg side and wide called
he angles it towards the off stump and Bravo was well forward to defend
half volley outside off and driven really hard to short cover, another fumble, costs a run
nice angle from Junaid, swinging and honing in on the stumps, Bravo was nicely behind the line to defend
he stays beside the line and defends towards point
he gives him more width outside off and Bravo gets forward and stylishly cuts wide of backward point
dragged it on! Gayle's horror form continues, Junaid gave him a bit of width and Gayle's foot movement was as good as nothing, half-heartedly poked his bat out and the inside edge hit the off stump
moves across and softly pushes it in front of his pads towards midwicket
lands on off and middle and he goes right across and defends
gets it to move across the right-hander and he doesn't offer a shot
this is testing stuff from Irfan, he gets it to angle awkwardly across the right-hander and add his sharp pace to that
gets it to angle much wider outside off, Samuels is happy to let it go
Samuels moves across to cover the line and gets an outside edge towards third man
drifts towards the leg side and he shuffles and clips it to fine leg
full outside off and driven confidently but straight to cover
good length on middle and off and he knocks it towards mid-on
slides down the leg side and wide called, Samuels moved a long way across
moves across and mistimes the punch towards mid-on

appeal for a catch down the leg side and he's given not out Akmal vehemently asks for a review and Misbah goes ahead with it, Samuels tries to glance it fine and there was a sound, looked like it brushed the thigh pad, no proof that it hit the bat so the decision stays
almost another edge, this one moves away and Samuels tries to drive
that should give Samuels a lot of confidence, full and on the off stump, he moves across and shows the full face of the bat and drives wide of mid-off, doesn't bother running
gets across and defends to the off side
he gets across and shoulders arms
hits a good length on the off stump and he stays back and defends
a bit too straight and he gets across and clips it to fine leg
Samuels gets a long way across and knocks it to the off side and thinks of a single
he angles it across the right-hander and he safely shoulders arms
pacy bouncer from Junaid, 137 kph, Bravo quickly ducks under that
Junaid struggles with his line and strays too wide down the leg side
that's a better line, on the off stump and Bravo gets across and defends
good length on the off stump and he stays back and defends
short of a length and Bravo gets across and defends
fuller in length outside off and he moves across and drives square on the off side
Junaid comes round the wicket, bowls it full on middle and leg and Samuels drives towards mid-on
good length outside off and Bravo moves across and defends
little shorter and he fends it off to the off side
he bangs it in far too short and Bravo ducks under that bouncer
a little short and he hops and defends
slashed away, this was wide outside off and a touch too full too, Bravo went forward and bashed it wide of backward point, uppish but safe
better line and length, closer to the off stump and he goes back and defends
another sharp delivery, short and quick and Samuels had to weave away to evade it
moves across and pushes it to the off side
fullish in length outside off and driven on the up towards cover
good length outside off and he cuts it down to backward point
fullish on the pads and flicked down to short midwicket, pretty well timed though
not a good start by Wahab, he strays down the leg side and Bravo easily helped it on its way down to fine leg
he angles it on the pads and he works it down to midwicket
lands it outside off and moves away, he safely leaves it alone

that was a misfield at the boundary alright but credit to Samuels for the way he timed and placed it, full outside off and he gets forward and across and times the square drive nicely past backward point, Jamshed slides and parries it to the deep backward point rope
gets across and pushes it to the off side
short of a length outside off and he stays back and defends
hits a good length outside off and he punches it towards mid-off
Bravo moves across and solidly defends to the off side
that one really took off of a good length, Bravo ducked quickly, no ball called
this was wide outside off and he dabs it down to third man
Samuels shuffles across and punches it wide of mid-on
that was a tester, Junaid hit the deck hard and Bravo was a  bit late in deciding to leave it alone, the ball just fizzed past the glove
shuffles across and tucks a length delivery to midwicket
Bravo tries to play a one-legged pull like Lara but it doesn't come off so well, it's in the air and falls safely at square leg
moves across and stabs it to the off side
lands it on middle and leg and he flicks it towards square leg
stays beside the line and pushes it towards point
this was short of a length and he hopped at the crease and knocked it to the on side
another bouncer penalised, Wahab hits the deck hard
short of length and Bravo is right behind the line to defend
full on the off stump and he thuds it down to mid-off
works it firmly towards midwicket
pushes it hard down the track and Hafeez stops it with the boot
driven firmly down the track again
stays back and he pushes it inside ougets a leading edge to the off side
flatter delivery, he gets forward and defends
fizzes away from the right-hander, Samuels decides not to play at it
good length outside off and he leaves it alone
on middle and off and he moves across and knocks it to the on side
extra bounce! Samuels fends it to the on side and the ball pops up off the shoulder of the bat, drops well short of Sohail at short square leg
moves right across and pushes it to the off side
Samuels circumspect again, moves across and fishes at one outside off, close to the edge
pushed through on off, defended back to the bowler
quicker one on off, the batsman goes on the back foot and pushes it to cover point
flighted delivery on off, he pushes forward to cover
slightly towards the pads, the batsman flicks it to long leg
quicker delivery on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler

this is the end of Lil Bravo!Another short delivery strikes gold today. Lil Bravo tried to nudge it to the leg side, but it was well directed and it kept rising on to him, the batsman was hit on the shoulder of the bat and it just lobbed up on the leg side. The fielder from square leg runs in and takes a good catch diving forward. It's the Prof there, he makes himself useful. Lil Bravo falls in his teens
length delivery angled away from the batsman, left alone
this one is too wide on the off side, the umpire stretches his arms
teasing line across the right-hander, he leaves it alone again
length delivery on off stump this time, the batsman defends it off the back foot
good delivery on a length just outside off, the batsman covers the line of the stumps and lets it go through
short of length delivery on off, the batsman defends it off the back foot
pushed through on off, punched to cover off the back foot
slower and tossed up, pushed back to the bowler
flighted and on the stumps, eased down to long on
pushed though on off, the batsman defends it off the back foot
tossed up and slower this time, the batsman comes forward and defends
full and flighted on the middle stump, driven back to the bowler
oh this one just whizzes past the outside edge! Not too far at all. The batsman tried to pull his bat back, but was mighty close to edging it
goes on the back foot to a length delivery, slides it to third man
interesting shot! It was short of length delivery on off, the batsman swats it to deep midwicket boundary. His bat came down from over his shoulder, and was swung down towards midwicket
length delivery angled across the batsman, left alone
pushes the length further and this is angled across too, left alone again
he goes on the back foot and defends the length delivery to point

this one is short and filthy outside off, the batsman goes on the back foot and punches it firmly in the gap at deep extra cover, but Wahab Riaz runs in from nowhere and makes an excellent diving stop at the boundary
he comes forward and defends the tossed up delivery to cover
full and flighted on middle stump, punched down the ground to long on
tossed up and full again, this one is driven past the non-striker for another single
pushed through on off stump, the batsman goes on the back foot and squeezes it out to deep backward point
he comes forward and pushes the length delivery to midwicket, where Misbah makes a good diving save
gets this one to slide in with the arm, but the batsman cuts it fine from close to his body, this one speeds to the third-man boundary
tossed up and slower on the stumps, the batsman comes forward and defends
full and on the stumps, driven back to the bowler
the batsman goes for a cut, but this is too close to the stumps, he chops it on to the pitch
he goes on the back foot and pushes this to long on
he comes forward and defends the slider back down the pitch
he goes on the back foot and punches it straight to mid-off
tossed up delivery on middle, the batsman drives it to long on
this one is pushed through, but it's down the leg side
quicker delivery aimed at leg stump, the batsman punches it to midwicket
tossed up and slower, on a length and it turns in a touch, the batsman defends it to cover
he comes forward and punches the length delivery down to long on
more flight this time, the batsman drives it straight to midwicket
he bowls this one full on the middle stump, driven to midwicket
he comes down the pitch and tries to whip it to the leg side, but gets hit in front of the stumps. The impact was outside off
quicker delivery on off, the batsman pushes it back to the bowler
shorter and quicker, the batsman defends it to the leg side
he goes on the back foot and punches the quicker delivery to deep point
another quicker delivery, the batsman cuts it to short third man
pushed through on the leg stump line, the batsman flicks it through backward square leg. Big Irfan does the clean-up job
he goes on the back foot this time and punches it to deep cover
shortish and on the pads, the batsman tucks it to deep backward square leg
he tries to smash this over the top, but it comes a touch quicker, he manages to drive that to midwicket
now he tries to go over the leg side again, but the bowler fires it on to his pads, he misses again
slower this time, the batsman pushes it to midwicket
he keeps this one on the stumps, the batsman comes forward and drives it to long on
fuller and quicker, pushed back to the bowler
slower, tossed up and this one turns a bit too. It hits the outside half of the bat and heads to short third man
quicker delivery outside off, the batsman defends it off the front foot
fuller and on the pads, the batsman skips down the track and times it though midwicket. It was in the air and went just over the outstretched hands of the fielder at midwicket.. Afridi not impressed
quicker delivery on off, pushed back to the bowler
tossed up delivery, pushed back to the bowler
he goes down on his knee to play a premeditated paddle and gets a bottom edge fine on the leg side
quicker delivery, spins in from a length, the batsman pushes it to point off the back foot
loud appeal for lbw, as this one turns in from outside off and hits the batsman in front. But there was a big inside edge and that wasn't too far from Umar.. goes down as a drop
beautiful delivery, this one doesn't turn much and whizzes past the outside edge
he takes a forward stride and defends the tossed up delivery
he gets some drift, but this one is easily defended off the back foot
he chooses to stay back to the slider and almost pays the price, the inside edge saves him
slightly tossed up and the batsman in no time swings his bat and sends this flying over deep midwicket.
fuller on off, the batsman comes forward and turns it to deep midwicket with a wristy push
he comes forward to defend, but doesn't read the slider. It keeps coming in and hits the inside edge
slightly short and that is what Samuels needs for some motivation.. He smacks it through point with some power
gets some big amount of turn from outside off, it hits the top of the pad, but was spinning down leg side
he goes on the back foot to this quicker delivery, defends to off
shorter length outside off, the batsman goes on the back foot and nudges it to backward point for a single
shorter, but turning in from outside off, the batsman pushes it to cover off the back foot
this was the doosra and the batsman does well to adjust to it by running it past the slip fielder
pushed through on the middle and leg line, defended to the leg side
he bowls it on short of length outside off, the batsman stands tall on his toes and punches it to deep cover
length delivery angled across the batsman, who leaves it alone
oii! This was too close to the outside edge as the batsman tries to run the angled delivery down to third man
short of length delivery on the middle and leg line, Marlon tucks it to square leg for a single
he goes on the back foot and pushes the back of length delivery through cover
this one is defended to point off the back foot. It stayed a touch low too
tossed up delivery on the stumps, defended to midwicket off the front foot
he goes down on his knee early and paddles the flighted delivery to fine leg
goes back and tucks this through midwicket
he comes on the front foot and drives this one to deep cover
tossed up outside off, the batsman comes forward and drives it firmly to deep over
he tries to play across the line to a top-spinner, but gets hit around his waist
the batsman opens up his stance in advance and the bowler bowls this wide outside off in response
length delivery on off, it's pushed softly towards mid-off, who is standing at the edge of the circle
he comes forward and drives the length delivery straight to mid-off
he bowls a short of length delivery and the batsman tucks it to square leg on the hop
he runs in hard and bowls a slower delivery, the batsman sees it late but adjusts well to defend it
short and only slightly wide, the batsman stands tall and chops it firmly past point

oh that was very close to being out! the batsman tries to jab this short of length delivery to the leg side, but it bounces a touch extra. It takes the top edge, hits the body and lobs to where the third slip would have been. Umar Akmal makes an attempt but it's a step too far
tossed up delivery, the batsman defends it to the leg side
he goes on the back foot and tucks this one towards midwicket
this one was the doosra and the batsman defends it off the back foot
an offspinner from outside off now, the batsman defends it again
he goes on the back foot to this sharply turning delivery and then pushes it to cover. Thinks about a single, but Samuels sends him back
slower and tossed up delivery on off, the batsman can't do much and he defends
length delivery outside off, the batsman drives it to off, but straight to the fielder at cover
length delivery angled across the batsman and that extra bounce that Irfan gets beats the bat
another length delivery just outside off, the batsman leaves it alone
back of length delivery on off, the batsman defends this to the off side
oye! That's a lifter from a short of length, the batsman sways away from it at the last moment
short ball, top edge has been the order of the day and Marlon joins in. But this one goes over the keeper's head and he is not as unlucky as others
he moves to 34 with a little paddle to fine leg this time
he goes on the back foot and punches the offspinning delivery down to long-on
he moves outside leg to make room, but is not able to squeeze the ball past cover
here comes the paddle sweep, he is not much in control, but manages to play it fine
bowls the doosra, which Marlon defends off the back foot
now comes the offspinner from outside off, the batsman is beaten by the turn
begins by punching the first ball down to mid-on
this was short and Simmons wanted to pull but edges it to his arm and the ball rolls to the keeper
not where he intended it to go, Simmons made room to smash that anywhere on the off side but ends up getting an inside edge that bounces past the keeper who dives
he makes room yet again to slash and he's beaten this time
angled outside off and he steers this wide of backward point, third man picks up
he bangs this one short and down the leg side and Samuels ducks, probably expecting a wide, shadow practices a pull
Simmons shows his intent by skipping down the track, checks his shot and drives to long-on
he makes room and cuts against the turn
goes back and Ajmal follows him, ends up mistiming it back to the bowler
more turn and he edges it between his legs, beats the keeper
stays back and he knocks it down to fine leg
he plonks forward and pushes it wide of cover, again just the single
he chops it hard down to backward point and Shehzad does well to leap and cut that off
brilliant fielding again, he made room and slashed on the up wide of Shehzad at backward point and Ajmal sprinted at the boundary and stopped that, looked like a certain four
low full toss and he makes room and pushes it wide of cover
that will relieve the pressure a bit, pitched up on middle and Simmons makes room and muscles it wide of midwicket
take that! Riaz pitched this one short but it was the length Simmons was looking for to make room and pull that flat over deep square leg
this time outside off and he cuts this one down to third man, 15 off this over
stays back and he pushes it to cover
goes back and punches against the turn, mid-off cuts it off
still insists on playing against the turn, can't beat cover
picks the doosra just in time, leading edge to the off side
tossed up and Simmons respects him by defending
tossed up and he defends again, still extra careful against Ajmal

Samuels' struggle ends, Irfan replaces Wahab and strikes immediately, pitches it on middle and leg and Samuels makes room and slash that over the off side, gets a thick edge to Akmal, more in desperation than anything else
stifled appeal for another caught behind, moving across the right-hander and he chases that one
with that extra slip Bravo is cautious and he shoulders arms
very good delivery in the Powerplay, on the channel outside off, steep bounce, Bravo can only leave it to the keeper
drifts on the pads and he gets off the mark with a clip behind square leg
angles wide across him and he opens the face of the bat and glides it to third man
straight and quick from Junaid, he can only punch it back to the bowler
drifts a bit on the pads and he clips it to the leg side
misses out on a low full toss, can only push it straight to Afridi at midwicket
fullish in length on the off stump and he can only push it down to mid-off
these dot balls not helping West Indies, good length on middle and leg and he clips it to square leg
Bravo tries to make something of this, forces it to the on side, beats midwicket, wants two but Afridi chases and limits it to a single
a bit too straight and he shuffles and clips it to short fine leg
cramps him for room and he can only punch it back to the bowler
shapes to smash that over the top and ends up getting a top edge down to third man
Simmons makes room and smashes that straight to mid-off, West Indies desperate for boundaries
this was full and wide outside off and he opens the face and runs it down to third man
teases him with width outside off and Bravo goes for the drive but misses
low full toss wide outside off and he makes room, gets an outside edge down to third man
they want to do this in singles, shuffles and clips it down to midwicket
more of those will help WI, this was a full ball outside leg, he made room and got an inside edge racing past the keeper
he makes room early and Junaid fires that wide outside off, doesn't offer a shot expecting a wide but the bowler was within the limits
nothing risky about that one, this was a low full toss outside off and he crashes that in the gap between mid-off and cover
tries the slower bouncer and Simmons pulls out of the stroke, Junaid was surprised by the wide call
he steers this one down to short third man and it's 12 off the over
slower ball from Riaz, lands full on middle and he drills it down to mid-off
fullish in length outside the off stump and he steers it down to third man
goes for the big swing and the top edge drops well short of third man
almost went all the way, this was a slower ball and dropped a bit short, Simmons made room and pulled behind square, one bounce and four
makes room and mistimes a low full toss down to cover

Dropped but a brilliant effort nevertheless from Hafeez, Simmons shaped to pull again but mistimed it and got a top edge that swirled over midwicket, Hafeez ran backward and threw himself at the ball but it failed to stick
Ajmal fires the quicker one and Simmons chooses to defend
he makes room and gets an inside edge to the on side

he has been given out LBW and Bravo wants to review it, pitches outside off and spins back in, Bravo was forward and he was struck above the knee roll, he had shuffled across his stumps, Hawkeye shows that clearing the leg stump, so on account of height Bravo survives
tossed up and he gets forward and pushes it to mid-on
he makes room and pushes it down to short third man
comes well forward and pushes it to the off side, another top over from Ajmal
Simmons continues to target the on side, only this time he gets a top edge that drops short of mid-off
Bravo goes for a slog and he misses it completely, Irfan's steep bounce and angle doing the trick
Bravo is struggling here, another slog and he connects with thin air
Bravo does the wise thing by shelving the slog and instead dabbing it to third man to get off strike
Simmons makes room and hits it in the air down to long-on and it drops short of the fielder
finally Bravo shows his class, Irfan pitches it up and Bravo picks it from the off stump and plays his stylish trademark flick down to deep midwicket
chips down the track and Ajmal cleverly fires it to the leg side, only a dot

brilliantly taken by Shehzad! Ajmal drops it fractionally short and Simmons goes for the pull, Shehzad ran to his left from deep midwicket, covered a lot of ground and timed his jump well, just managed to hang on and he hurt himself after taking the catch
strays down the leg side
Bravo just about managed to read that doosra, defended
two for the over! Bravo made room early to crash that through the off side, Ajmal bowled that flat and quick, Bravo had exposed his stumps, failed to connect and the ball hit the leg stump
stays back and turns it to the on side
Pollard can only softly defend that, Ajmal really throttling WI here
that was far too wide outside off
great attempt by Misbah, Sammy made room and smashed that, Misbah threw himself to his left at cover and saved a certain four
comes round the wicket this time, good delivery there, on the blockhole and Sammy can only dig it out

timber! The off stump is down, full credit to Junaid as he fires in a yorker from round the wicket (Akram would have been proud of this), Pollard made room and failed to get his bat down, the off stump lands about 3 yards back
pushes a full delivery towards cover and picks up a quick single
well there's still hope as long as Sammy's there, this is a low full toss and Sammy stays at the crease and clubs it over deep midwicket

6 and out! Sammy tries to go big once again, Junaid pitches it on a good length, Sammy stays at the crease and tries to club it over long-on, didn't get the elevation, hammers it flat to Hafeez at long-on
no problems for Narine! Ajmal tosses it up and Narine smacks it over long-off
early panic for Ajmal! Narine hammers a flatter delivery towards long-on and Riaz at the boundary didn't really see it, in fact nobody chased it
Ajmal bowls it slower and Narine swings early and misses
Narine showing how to tackle Ajmal, tossed up and Narine comes forward and launches it clean down the ground, just short of the long-off rope
and Ajmal hits back! What an over this has been, Ajmal bowls a flatter off break, Narine tries to swing it over midwicket, misses and the ball shaves the off stump
stays back and clips it down to short fine leg
comes round the wicket and Holder carves that over point
angles this one towards leg and he swivels and forces it behind, fine effort by Wahab at the fine leg boundary
fires that full outside off and he gets an outside edge to third man
full and on the stumps and he can only hammer it back to the bowler
Roach hasn't given up yet, this was pitched up on middle and leg and Roach makes room and forces it past midwicket
Junaid responds well with a yorker fired outside off, too quick for Roach to get his bat down and make something of it
close call for Pakistan first up as Holder gets on outside edge past the keeper, third man is more fine so he could cut that off
that was quite a clean strike by Roach but Misbah was alert at cover to cut that off

oh well six off the over already! Wahab goes over the wicket and pitches it up, Holder makes room and drives crisply wide of cover, for some reason the boundaries are not as protected as they should be
some respite for Wahab as he shortens the length down the leg side and Holder swings and misses
hang on! Holder knocks off 6 of those! Wahab bowling length, Holder makes room and carves that clean over extra cover, seriously that was not a fluke hit from a No.11, it was a genuine shot

and it's a tie would you believe it! Wahab aims to pitch it fuller on the stumps and doesn't quite succeed, Holder swings and he gets a thick edge that goes past the keeper and races to third man, the throw from Junaid was to the keeper Akmal who didn't collect it at all, not sure what went wrong with Akmal because it wasn't exactly the worst throw
